The National Association of Nigerian Students (NANS) on Monday stormed Abuja to resume its protest to demand an end to the ongoing strike by the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU). The National President of NANS, Sunday Asefon who spoke during the protest said that the union as well as the students are ready to throng major roads in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). Speaking further, he affirmed that the students are resolute and would not retreat until universities across the country are reopened. Heb said, “Since they have sent us out of our lecture rooms we would convert the streets and roads of FCT to our lecture rooms. “This is not a child’s play, we mean business this time around. Our message is simple: Reopen our universities. we are resolute if this strike is not called off, Nigerian Students are not leaving the streets. “We are resuming here not minding what happens. FCT residents should be notified that we are taking to the major roads as part of measures to demand our schools should be reopened.”